properties.sfomuseum:description: Airmail flight cover, part of International Tributes to the History of Flight series by the Postal Commemorative Society; white envelope with full color illustration cachet and inset stamp commemorating first commercial SST flight on December 26, 1975, in Moscow, U.S.S.R., by Tupolev with TU-144 supersonic transport aircraft; cancellation stamp dated December 26, 1985 in Moscow; includes information on reverse.
